==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: world-wide web
<hw>world"-wide` web"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
collective total of all computer installations that are connected to the
internet and provide access to other computers connected to the
internet, using <er>hypertext transfer protocol</er>, to computer files
called <part>web pages</part>, which may have text, graphics, audio or
animated video data, as well as pages which may provide data or
information in all those forms.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Web, the web, WWW.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worm</ent>⟦br⟧
